\pard\f0\fs28 Erect perennials. Petals contorted in bud. Epicalyx absent. Calyx 10-veined, with 5 short teeth. Limb of petal more or less distinct from claw; coronal scales present. Stamens 10, rarely up to 20; styles usually 5, opposite calyx-teeth. Fruit a capsule, dehiscing with (usually) 5 teeth. Carpophore short or long. Seeds without a tuft of hairs at hilum. (Incl.{\i  Coronaria} Schaeffer, {\i Polyschemone }Schott, {\i Viscaria} Bernh.)
