\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. chalcedonica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 436 (1753). Stems 30-45(-60) cm, simple, stout, hispid. Leaves sparsely hispid, ovate, acute; the cauline cordate-amplexicaul. Inflorescence 10- to 50-flowered, capitate. Calyx 14-17 mm. Petal-limb bright scarlet, bifid for 1/3 of its length. Carpophore 4-6 mm. {\i Woods and thickets. C. & E. Russia from c.} 49°{\i  to }56°{\i  N. }Rs(C, E).
\par

