\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. L. flos-jovis} (L.) Desr. in Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot. }{\b 3:} 644 (1792). Less densely villous than {\b 2}; stems 20-90 cm, usually erect and little-branched. Basal leaves lanceolate-spathulate, acute; cauline lanceolate. Inflorescence 4- to 10-flowered, more or less capitate. Calyx 11-13 mm. Petal-limb purplish or scarlet, rarely white, bifid with wide, often lobed, lobes. Capsule c. 14 mm; carpophore c. 2 mm.{\i  Dry, sunny slopes,} 1000-2000{\i  m. Alps, eastwards to c. }11° 15'{\i  E.; one station in C. Italy.} ?Au Ge He It [Cz].
