\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. L. sibirica} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 437 (1753). Whole plant pubescent with short, crispate hairs. Stems 8-30 cm, usually simple. Basal leaves crowded on woody stock, linear-lanceolate; cauline 3-8 pairs, remote. Inflorescence (1-)3- to 4(-8)-flowered, lax; pedicels mostly longer than calyx. Calyx 5-6(-8) mm. Petal-limb pale yellow or white, bifid to about half-way; coronal scales lanceolate, acute. Capsule 6-8 mm; carpophore very short.{\i  Arctic and subarctic Russia.} Rs (N). ({\i N. Asia })
\par

