\pard\f0\fs28 The European plant is subsp.{\b  samojedorum} Sambuk,{\i  Bull. Acad. Sci. URSS} ser. 7, {\b 22: }47 (1928) ({\i L. samojedorum} (Sambuk) Gorschk.). Subsp. {\i sibirica} occurs in Siberia and approaches close to the boundary of Europe north-east of Sverdlovsk.
