\pard\f0\fs28 Very variable, the centre of variation being in Makedonija. To the north and west of this region, the plants have a long carpophore, and in Greece only plants with a short carpophore occur. The shape of the calyx is more or less correlated with the length of the carpophore, but the other variable characters are not. Two subspecies can be recognized.
